        "type": "text",
        "text": "Now let me update the triage table with the two new NDAs:\n\n| # | Counterparty | Verdict | Top Issues | Action |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | ACME Tooling Solutions | **GREEN** | None | Sign without legal review |\n| 2 | BetaCorp Logistics | **YELLOW** | Long survival (7yr post-term), broad CI definition, no-publicity clause | Legal review & redline |\n| 3 | Cypress Systems | **RED** | Perpetual term, no residuals carve-out, no-reverse-engineering clause, California jurisdiction | Escalate to GC |\n| 4 | Delphi Components | **GREEN** | None | Sign without legal review |\n| 5 | Emberlake Holdings | **YELLOW** | Overbroad CI definition, limited carve-outs, non-solicitation clause (12mo) | Legal review & redline |\n| 6 | Folium Research Institute | **GREEN** | None | Sign without legal review |\n| 7 | Greenline ERP | **RED** | Perpetual term, no residuals carve-out, non-compete (2yr), liquidated damages ($500k), Texas exclusive jurisdiction | Escalate to GC |\n| 8 | Harborwave Cloud Services | **GREEN** | None | Sign without legal review |\n| 9 | Iris Consulting Group | **YELLOW** | Long survival (10yr post-term), non-solicitation clause (12mo) | Legal review & redline |\n| 10 | Jadestone Manufacturing | **GREEN** | None | Sign without legal review |\n\n---\n\n## Updated Summary — 10 NDAs triaged\n\n**Sign immediately (Greens — 5 NDAs):**\n- ACME Tooling\n- Delphi Components\n- Folium Research\n- Harborwave Cloud Services\n- Jadestone Manufacturing\n\n**Send to legal for redline (Yellows — 3 NDAs):**\n- BetaCorp Logistics\n- Emberlake Holdings\n- Iris Consulting Group\n\n**Escalate to GC (Red — 2 NDAs):**\n- Cypress Systems\n- Greenline ERP\n\n---\n\n## Detail on new YELLOW & RED items:\n\n**Greenline ERP (RED):**\n- **Perpetual term** (Clause 3): \"Stanford's obligations under this Agreement shall survive in perpetuity\" with \"no termination date and obligations do not lapse.\" This alone is disqualifying — creates indefinite liability exposure.\n- **No residuals carve-out** (Clause 4): Explicitly states \"There is no carve-out for residual information retained in the unaided memory of Stanford's personnel.\" This overreach prevents normal use of general knowledge retained by staff.\n- **Non-compete clause** (Clause 5): 2-year post-term restriction on engagement with competing ERP suppliers. This is a market-restriction clause dressed as confidentiality — belongs in a separate employment or exclusivity agreement, not an NDA. Red flag.\n- **Liquidated damages** (Clause 6): $500k per incident is a penalty clause and signals the drafter intends to extract value rather than protect legitimate secrets.\n- **Texas exclusive jurisdiction**: Combined with other issues, adds cost-of-litigation concern.\n\n**Do not sign Greenline. Perpetual term + non-compete + liquidated damages = GC escalation required.**\n\n**Iris Consulting Group (YELLOW):**\n- **Long survival** (Clause 4): 3-year operative + **10-year post-term survival**. The 10-year tail is excessive. Playbook threshold is 7 years combined. Redline to 3 years operative + 3-year survival (6 total).\n- **Non-solicitation clause** (Clause 5): 12-month post-term restriction on solicitation of \"any employee...with whom it has had contact during the Purpose.\" This is beyond-confidentiality overreach (belongs in employment agreement), but the 12-month window and narrow trigger (\"direct contact\") make it negotiable. Flag it but not disqualifying. If Iris pushes back hard, you can live with 6 months.\n- **Otherwise standard**: CI definition is reasonable, carve-outs are present, England & Wales law is acceptable.\n\n---\n\nAll four new NDAs have been added to the full batch triage. GREEN and YELLOW items are ready for your decision; RED items (Greenline) require GC sign-off before any response to the counterparty."
